/wiki/Socialist_Party_of_Serbia: The Socialist Party of Serbia (Serbian: Социјалистичка партија Србије, romanized: Socijalistička partija Srbije; abbr. СПС or SPS) is a left-wing populist political party in Serbia that identifies as democratic socialist and social-democratic. The Socialist Party of Serbia was the direct descendant of the League of Communists of Serbia. Throughout its existence, the party has utilised some nationalist rhetoric and themes, and has therefore been labelled a Serbian nationalist party, although the SPS has never identified itself as such.
/wiki/Dragan_Jovanovi\u0107_(Yugoslav_po: Dragan Jovanović (Serbian Cyrillic: Драган Јовановић) was a cabinet minister in the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia during the early 1990s.
/wiki/Independent_politician: An independent or nonpartisan politician is a politician not affiliated with any political party. There are numerous reasons why someone may stand for office as an independent.
/wiki/Democratic_Party_of_Socialists_of_: The Democratic Party of Socialists of Montenegro (Montenegrin: Demokratska partija socijalista Crne Gore / Демократска партија социјалиста Црне Горе, DPS) is the ruling political party in Montenegro. It has been so since the introduction of a multi-party system in 1990.
/wiki/Dragi\u0161a_Pe\u0161i\u0107: Dragiša Pešić (Serbian: Драгиша Пешић; 8 August 1954 – 8 September 2016) was a Montenegrin politician. He was the second last Prime Minister of  Federal Republic of Yugoslavia
/wiki/Socialist_People's_Party_of_Monten: The Socialist People's Party of Montenegro (Montenegrin: Социјалистичка народна партија Црне Горе / Socijalistička narodna partija Crne Gore) is a socially conservative social-democratic opposition political party in Montenegro. It is part of the Key Coalition, an opposition political alliance in Montenegro.  It has 2 (in the Parliament of Montenegro) of 3 MPs which it won in the 2016 parliamentary election. The party is pro-European Union and anti-NATO.
/wiki/Democratic_Party_of_Serbia: The Democratic Party of Serbia (Serbian: Демократска странка Србије / Demokratska stranka Srbije, pronounced [demǒkratskaː strânka sr̂bije], Serbian abbreviation: ДCC / DSS) is a national-conservative, Christian-democratic political party in Serbia.
/wiki/G17_Plus: G17 Plus (G17+), was a liberal-conservative political party in Serbia that existed from 2002 until 2013 when it merged into the United Regions of Serbia (URS).
/wiki/Ministry_of_Finance_(Yugoslavia): The Ministry of Finance of Yugoslavia refers to the finance ministry which was responsible for financial system of the Kingdom of Yugoslavia from 1918 to 1945 and the communist SFR Yugoslavia from 1945 to 1992. It may also refer to the finance ministry of Serbia and Montenegro (officially named the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia) from 1992 to 2003.
